cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the optimization of loss functions for deep neural networks. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as top-k classification is a common measure of performance in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the optimization of neural networks. Finally, it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it presents a novel algorithm for evaluating the proposed loss functions.
